<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Remarks.</emphasis>
Based on distribution data gathered from the literature and studied specimens, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1888" box="[1203,1351,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[1203,1351,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">M. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Q. Liu &amp; Q. Liu" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">M. acutulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are nearly sympatric. The host plant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1888" box="[693,840,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis box="[693,840,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">M. castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unknown so far.
</paragraph>
